# QPC Virtual Clinic — operator binding

## Public mount (world-facing)

**The clinic project is mounted at:** [https://qpc.shaneturon.ca](https://qpc.shaneturon.ca)

When the user asks where the clinic is mounted, deployed, live, or “for the world to see” — **answer this URL first.** One line. No NOTEBOOKLM_CONTEXT, no `~/ShipYard`, no `~/mnt/gdrive` unless they ask for code or files next.

| Question type | Answer first |
|---------------|--------------|
| Where is the clinic live / mounted? | `https://qpc.shaneturon.ca` |
| Where is the code? | `~/ShipYard/projects/qpc-virtual-clinic/apps/qpc-clinic/` |
| Where are work orders on Drive? | `QPC Virtual Clinic + Website/work-orders/` |

## Instruction precedence

1. **User’s explicit path or URL** in the current message  
2. This rule (QPC public URL + Drive folder above)  
3. CONTROL TOWER / NOTEBOOKLM_CONTEXT defaults  

If (1) and (3) conflict, **do not** silently follow (3). Ask once or follow (1).

## Forbidden habits

- Do not lead with protocol trees, execution mirrors, or rclone paths when the user means the **clinic website**.  
- Do not copy or sync to Drive unless the user asks.  
- Do not create a second canonical location without stating it and getting alignment.

## Deploy status

If `qpc.shaneturon.ca` is not yet serving the app, say so **after** giving the URL as the target mount, then what blocks deploy (one sentence).
